00:24:08.358 --> 00:24:12.144
Then he began to teach
them, then he began to

00:24:12.144 --> 00:24:15.673
teach them--not before--"
Then He began to teach them

00:24:15.673 --> 00:24:18.269
that the Son of Man must undergo
great suffering,

00:24:18.269 --> 00:24:20.190
be rejected by the elders,
the chief priest,

00:24:20.190 --> 00:24:22.711
the Scribes,
and be killed and after three

00:24:22.711 --> 00:24:23.819
days rise again.
 

00:24:23.819 --> 00:24:27.059
He said all this quite openly.
 

00:24:27.059 --> 00:24:29.588
Mark is a clever writer.
 

00:24:29.588 --> 00:24:32.609
He puts little short sentences
like this in his gospel at

00:24:32.609 --> 00:24:35.307
interesting places,
and you the reader are supposed

00:24:35.307 --> 00:24:37.519
to go, okay he's talking right
to me.

00:24:37.519 --> 00:24:39.515
"He said this
openly,"

00:24:39.515 --> 00:24:42.281
it's not closed anymore,
this part's opened,

00:24:42.281 --> 00:24:44.019
this part's not closed.
 

00:24:44.019 --> 00:24:47.220
It's not going to be the end of
the problem.

00:24:47.220 --> 00:24:49.308
"Peter took him aside and
began to rebuke him.

00:24:49.308 --> 00:24:51.872
But turning and looking at his
disciples he rebuked

00:24:51.872 --> 00:24:52.588
Peter."
 

00:24:52.588 --> 00:24:54.423
Peter is of course saying
something like,

00:24:54.423 --> 00:24:55.661
"No, no,
no, no, Jesus,

00:24:55.661 --> 00:24:56.670
you didn't get it.
 

00:24:56.670 --> 00:24:58.788
We just said you're the Messiah.
 

00:24:58.788 --> 00:25:01.778
The Messiah doesn't suffer and
die on a cross;

00:25:01.778 --> 00:25:04.588
the Messiah comes with angels
and rules the world.

00:25:04.588 --> 00:25:06.098
The Messiah overthrows the
Romans.

00:25:06.098 --> 00:25:08.382
The Messiah sets up the new
reconstituted Israel,

00:25:08.382 --> 00:25:10.759
and all the nations will flock
to Jerusalem now.

00:25:10.759 --> 00:25:12.470
You're the Messiah,
that's what you do.

00:25:12.470 --> 00:25:16.116
No, you don't suffer and die,
that's not what Messiah's

00:25:16.116 --> 00:25:16.858
do."
 

00:25:16.858 --> 00:25:20.730
There's no Jewish expectation
in the ancient world that the

00:25:20.730 --> 00:25:22.798
Messiah would suffer and die.
 

00:25:22.798 --> 00:25:25.028
Modern Christians think,
well that's--

00:25:25.028 --> 00:25:26.640
of course it's all the way
through the Old Testament,

00:25:26.640 --> 00:25:29.105
but those prophecies and
things, those statements and

00:25:29.105 --> 00:25:31.663
poems in the Old Testament,
they weren't taken to be about

00:25:31.663 --> 00:25:33.818
the Messiah they were taken to
be about other prophets,

00:25:33.818 --> 00:25:35.990
or holy men of God who might
have to suffer,

00:25:35.990 --> 00:25:37.210
who might be persecuted.
 

00:25:37.210 --> 00:25:41.130
The Messiah passages don't have
suffering and death in them;

00:25:41.130 --> 00:25:45.048
they just refer to this coming
King, the descendent of David.

00:25:45.048 --> 00:25:48.788
No Jews in the first century
this time expected that the

00:25:48.788 --> 00:25:50.759
Messiah would be crucified.
 

00:25:50.759 --> 00:25:53.338
It just was absolutely against
common sense.

00:25:53.338 --> 00:25:56.896
Messiahs don't suffer,
Messiahs aren't crucified,

00:25:56.896 --> 00:25:58.750
Messiahs aren't beaten.
 

00:25:58.750 --> 00:26:04.015
Peter actually quite
understandably thinks that Jesus

00:26:04.015 --> 00:26:05.940
has got it wrong.
 

00:26:05.940 --> 00:26:09.248
Peter says, You're the Messiah,
you're not going to be killed

00:26:09.248 --> 00:26:11.660
and suffer,
and that's when Jesus turns

00:26:11.660 --> 00:26:14.819
around and rebukes Peter looking
at His disciples--

00:26:14.819 --> 00:26:15.990
is that an interesting clue?
 

00:26:15.990 --> 00:26:19.019
that Jesus is looking at his
disciples and he rebukes Peter?

00:26:19.019 --> 00:26:23.837
"Get behind me,
Satan, for you are setting your

00:26:23.837 --> 00:26:28.940
mind not on divine things but on
human things."

00:26:28.940 --> 00:26:31.630
That's a very interesting story
in itself.

00:26:31.630 --> 00:26:36.568
What is Jesus rebuking Peter
for and calling him Satan?

00:26:36.568 --> 00:26:39.910
He called the crowd with his
disciples,

00:26:39.910 --> 00:26:43.904
and said to them,
"If any want to become my

00:26:43.904 --> 00:26:46.946
followers,
let them deny themselves and

00:26:46.946 --> 00:26:49.368
take up their cross and follow
me.

00:26:49.368 --> 00:26:52.498
For those who want to save
their life will lose it,

00:26:52.498 --> 00:26:56.315
and those who lose their life
for my sake, and for the sake of

00:26:56.315 --> 00:26:58.130
the gospel, will save it.
 

00:26:58.130 --> 00:27:00.955
For what will it profit them to
gain the whole world and forfeit

00:27:00.955 --> 00:27:01.538
their life?
 

00:27:01.538 --> 00:27:05.259
Indeed, what can they give in
return for their life?

00:27:05.259 --> 00:27:08.132
Those who are ashamed of me and
of my words in this adulteress

00:27:08.132 --> 00:27:10.681
and sinful generation,
of them the Son of Man will

00:27:10.681 --> 00:27:13.680
also be ashamed when he comes in
the glory of his angels--

00:27:13.680 --> 00:27:15.759
of his Father with the holy
angels."

00:27:15.759 --> 00:27:17.598
[That's what Messiah's were
expected to do,

00:27:17.598 --> 00:27:20.123
is come in glory with holy
angels.]

00:27:20.123 --> 00:27:23.336
And he said to them,
"Truly I tell you there

00:27:23.336 --> 00:27:26.619
are some standing here who will
not taste death until they see

00:27:26.619 --> 00:27:29.150
that the kingdom of God has come
with power.

00:27:29.150 --> 00:27:30.490
What's going on here?
 

00:27:30.490 --> 00:27:33.957
You have the correct
identification of Jesus,

00:27:33.957 --> 00:27:37.108
even according to Mark as the
Messiah.

00:27:37.108 --> 00:27:39.769
You have the charge to secrecy
in 8:30;

00:27:39.769 --> 00:27:42.064
you have the passion
prediction--one of the passion

00:27:42.064 --> 00:27:44.910
predictions and the first of
several that we'll see in Mark.

00:27:44.910 --> 00:27:46.529
Jesus saying,
this is going to happen,

00:27:46.529 --> 00:27:49.621
and then you have this word,
"And he said this plainly

00:27:49.621 --> 00:27:52.180
and clearly to them,"
a nice little clue.

00:27:52.180 --> 00:27:54.618
Then you have Peter's
misunderstanding,

00:27:54.618 --> 00:27:56.930
but what does Peter
misunderstand?

00:27:56.930 --> 00:27:57.950
That's what we'll ask.
 

00:27:57.950 --> 00:28:00.308
What was Peter expecting
different?

00:28:00.308 --> 00:28:02.217
Well he was expecting the
Messiah to come with angels and

00:28:02.217 --> 00:28:02.660
triumphant.
 

00:28:02.660 --> 00:28:06.037
Then you have an emphasis on
suffering that everybody has to

00:28:06.037 --> 00:28:07.961
suffer,
not just the Son of Man,

00:28:07.961 --> 00:28:11.457
but everybody has to suffer and
you have a prediction of future

00:28:11.457 --> 00:28:12.808
eschatological glory.
 

00:28:12.808 --> 00:28:16.336
Eschatology is just a fancy
theological word meaning the end

00:28:16.336 --> 00:28:18.490
times, the study of the end
times.

00:28:18.490 --> 00:28:21.441
Eschaton is just a Greek
word meaning "the

00:28:21.441 --> 00:28:22.108
end."
 

00:28:22.108 --> 00:28:29.343
You'll see this if you read
much about the Bible or ancient

00:28:29.343 --> 00:28:32.595
religion,
the eschaton will come up

00:28:32.595 --> 00:28:36.061
apocalyptic contexts,
and eschatology means any study

00:28:36.061 --> 00:28:39.288
or doctrine about the end of the
world as we know it.

00:28:39.288 --> 00:28:41.830
In fact I used to direct a
little singing group in the

00:28:41.830 --> 00:28:44.230
Divinity School when I was a
grad student here,

00:28:44.230 --> 00:28:46.500
and we called ourselves
"The Eschatones."

00:28:46.500 --> 00:28:53.460
A joke that only divinity
students would get.

00:28:53.460 --> 00:28:56.977
The prediction of the
eschatological glory that comes

00:28:56.977 --> 00:29:00.020
after the suffering and then
right after that,

00:29:00.020 --> 00:29:01.405
6:2:
Six days later,

00:29:01.405 --> 00:29:03.682
Jesus took with him Peter and
James and John,

00:29:03.682 --> 00:29:06.528
led them up to a high mountain
apart, by themselves.

00:29:06.528 --> 00:29:09.105
And he was transfigured before
them, and his clothes became

00:29:09.105 --> 00:29:11.058
dazzling white,
such as no one on earth could

00:29:11.058 --> 00:29:11.769
bleach them.
 

00:29:11.769 --> 00:29:14.505
And there appeared to them
Elijah with Moses,

00:29:14.505 --> 00:29:16.368
who were talking with Jesus.
 

00:29:16.368 --> 00:29:19.534
Then Peter said to Jesus,
"Rabbi it's good for us to

00:29:19.534 --> 00:29:21.559
be here;
let us make three dwellings

00:29:21.559 --> 00:29:23.290
[three tabernacles,
three tents],

00:29:23.290 --> 00:29:24.696
one for you,
one for Moses,

00:29:24.696 --> 00:29:26.318
and one for Elijah."
 

00:29:26.318 --> 00:29:28.430
He did not know what to say for
they were terrified.

00:29:28.430 --> 00:29:30.973
Then a cloud overshadowed them,
and from the cloud there came a

00:29:30.973 --> 00:29:32.740
voice, "This is my Son,
the Beloved;

00:29:32.740 --> 00:29:34.048
listen to him!"
 

00:29:34.048 --> 00:29:36.795
Suddenly when they looked
around, they saw no one with

00:29:36.795 --> 00:29:38.348
them anymore but only Jesus.
 

00:29:38.348 --> 00:29:40.878
[The next verse:]
"As they were coming down

00:29:40.878 --> 00:29:43.624
the mountain,
he ordered them to tell no one

00:29:43.624 --> 00:29:46.863
what they had seen [--
again that secrecy motif--]

00:29:46.863 --> 00:29:49.920
until the Son of Man had risen
from the dead.

00:29:49.920 --> 00:29:51.630
And again an emphasis on death.
 

00:29:51.630 --> 00:29:53.650
What's going on with all this?
 

00:29:53.650 --> 00:29:56.702
What's going on is that Mark is
trying to make an important

00:29:56.702 --> 00:29:59.650
point, maybe even to his fellow
believers at the time.

00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:06.556
Apparently, what Peter doesn't
understand about Jesus is that

00:30:06.556 --> 00:30:10.930
Jesus has to suffer and has to
die,

00:30:10.930 --> 00:30:13.740
and if that causes a
redefinition of Peter's notion

00:30:13.740 --> 00:30:16.230
of what a Messiah is,
so be it.

00:30:16.230 --> 00:30:20.207
Peter needs to work with a
redefined notion of the Christ,

00:30:20.207 --> 00:30:22.788
the Messiah,
if he doesn't include the

00:30:22.788 --> 00:30:25.720
necessity of suffering in that
notion.

00:30:25.720 --> 00:30:30.490
Let's imagine the context for
this kind of message.

00:30:30.490 --> 00:30:34.108
The rapid fire style of Mark is
one of the--

00:30:34.108 --> 00:30:35.702
if you notice--did you notice
how many times

00:30:35.702 --> 00:30:37.000
"immediately"
is used,

00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:38.029
the word
"immediately"?

00:30:38.029 --> 00:30:41.002
The writer of the Gospel of
Mark needed a good Yale college

00:30:41.002 --> 00:30:43.942
editor or a writing tutor,
because there's kind of a rapid

00:30:43.942 --> 00:30:45.372
fire,
it's not reading very good

00:30:45.372 --> 00:30:46.220
Greek style either.
 

00:30:46.220 --> 00:30:47.268
It's rapid fire,
he says, immediately this

00:30:47.268 --> 00:30:48.828
happened, then immediately this
happened, and then immediately

00:30:48.828 --> 00:30:49.288
this happened.
 

00:30:49.288 --> 00:30:52.003
You get the idea reading the
Gospel of Mark that the

00:30:52.003 --> 00:30:54.878
narrative is pulling you along,
it's shoving you along,

00:30:54.878 --> 00:30:56.210
is rushing you along.
 

00:30:56.210 --> 00:30:59.269
That's actually part of,
I think, this apocalyptic style

00:30:59.269 --> 00:31:02.662
of Mark, because the Gospel of
Mark is also apocalyptic in its

00:31:02.662 --> 00:31:03.328
message.
 

00:31:03.328 --> 00:31:05.088
It talks about angels coming at
the end;

00:31:05.088 --> 00:31:07.755
it talks about a big war that's
going to happen,

00:31:07.755 --> 00:31:11.157
so you have demons and a battle
of Jesus with the strong man,

00:31:11.157 --> 00:31:12.858
another apocalyptic story.
 

00:31:12.858 --> 00:31:15.515
You have the emphasis on
suffering and persecution,

00:31:15.515 --> 00:31:18.170
and that's a common theme of
Jewish apocalyptic.

00:31:18.170 --> 00:31:20.775
Not that the Messiah would
suffer but that the Jews

00:31:20.775 --> 00:31:23.953
themselves might have to suffer
before the fabulous kingdom of

00:31:23.953 --> 00:31:24.838
the end time.
 

00:31:24.838 --> 00:31:27.763
Remember you saw it in Daniel,
when we read Daniel two classes

00:31:27.763 --> 00:31:29.910
ago,
Daniel predicts suffering for

00:31:29.910 --> 00:31:32.123
the righteous,
and only after the suffering

00:31:32.123 --> 00:31:35.200
would you have the goodies,
heaven, the Kingdom of God.

00:31:35.200 --> 00:31:38.106
Now we'll look at Mark 13 and
we're going to analyze it pretty

00:31:38.106 --> 00:31:38.680
carefully.
 

00:31:38.680 --> 00:31:42.130
Again some of these things will
come into play.

00:31:42.130 --> 00:31:45.902
The basic message I'm saying is
that people misunderstand about

00:31:45.902 --> 00:31:49.733
Jesus is that they misunderstand
the necessity of suffering that

00:31:49.733 --> 00:31:53.259
must be there before you--
must precede glory.

00:31:53.259 --> 00:31:56.345
Yes, God promises them glory,
they're going to be glorified

00:31:56.345 --> 00:31:58.596
in the end,
they're going to win in the

00:31:58.596 --> 00:32:01.720
end, but they have to go through
a period of suffering.

00:32:01.720 --> 00:32:04.160
Jesus is the first one who does
this,

00:32:04.160 --> 00:32:08.069
he accepts suffering and death
before he himself is glorified

00:32:08.069 --> 00:32:10.892
but the glory will come,
it has to be preceded by

00:32:10.892 --> 00:32:11.380
suffering.
 

00:32:11.380 --> 00:32:13.708
But Jesus also in Mark tells
the disciples over and over

00:32:13.708 --> 00:32:15.703
again,
you also will have to

00:32:15.703 --> 00:32:18.538
suffer first,
but if you endure you will

00:32:18.538 --> 00:32:20.279
experience glory also.
 

00:32:20.279 --> 00:32:24.700
Now look at Mark 13.
 

00:32:24.700 --> 00:32:27.630
As he came out of the temple,
one of his disciples said to

00:32:27.630 --> 00:32:28.884
Him,
"Look, Teacher,

00:32:28.884 --> 00:32:31.118
what large stones and what
large buildings!"

00:32:31.118 --> 00:32:33.698
Then Jesus asked him,
"Do you see these great

00:32:33.698 --> 00:32:34.328
buildings?
 

00:32:34.328 --> 00:32:37.019
Not one stone will be left here
upon another;

00:32:37.019 --> 00:32:38.470
all will be thrown down."
 

00:32:38.470 --> 00:32:41.209
[He's predicting the
destruction of the temple in

00:32:41.209 --> 00:32:43.319
Jerusalem.]
When he was sitting on the

00:32:43.319 --> 00:32:45.660
Mount of Olives opposite the
temple,

00:32:45.660 --> 00:32:47.571
Peter, James,
John, and Andrew asked him

00:32:47.571 --> 00:32:48.930
privately,
"Tell us,

00:32:48.930 --> 00:32:51.230
when will this be,
and what will be the sign that

00:32:51.230 --> 00:32:53.220
all these things are to be
accomplished?"

00:32:53.220 --> 00:32:56.034
Then Jesus began to say to
them, "Beware that no one

00:32:56.034 --> 00:32:56.990
leads you astray.
 

00:32:56.990 --> 00:32:59.410
Many will come in my name and
say, "I am he!"

00:32:59.410 --> 00:33:00.880
and they will lead many astray.
 

00:33:00.880 --> 00:33:03.151
False prophets,
Jesus predicts there will be

00:33:03.151 --> 00:33:05.316
false prophets,
maybe even false Messiahs,

00:33:05.316 --> 00:33:08.009
although he doesn't use that
term here in Mark.

00:33:08.009 --> 00:33:10.230
It will occur in other places.
 

00:33:10.230 --> 00:33:13.028
When you hear of wars and
rumors of wars,

00:33:13.028 --> 00:33:15.632
do not be alarmed;
this must take place,

00:33:15.632 --> 00:33:17.348
but the end is still to come.
 

00:33:17.348 --> 00:33:20.288
So just when people have--when
times are bad and there are wars

00:33:20.288 --> 00:33:23.226
that's not necessarily the end
yet, you've got to have a few of

00:33:23.226 --> 00:33:23.700
those.
 

00:33:23.700 --> 00:33:26.068
For nation will rise against
nation, kingdom against kingdom;

00:33:26.068 --> 00:33:27.359
there will be earthquakes in
various places;

00:33:27.359 --> 00:33:28.348
there will be famines.
 

00:33:28.348 --> 00:33:31.420
This is but the beginning of
the birth pangs.

00:33:31.420 --> 00:33:34.480
As for yourselves, beware;
for they will hand you over to

00:33:34.480 --> 00:33:35.586
counsels;
and you will be beaten in

00:33:35.586 --> 00:33:35.960
synagogues.
 

00:33:35.960 --> 00:33:37.328
Again this theme of suffering.
 

00:33:37.328 --> 00:33:39.108
You have all these terrible
cosmic events,

00:33:39.108 --> 00:33:42.058
terrible wars and disasters,
earthquakes and all that sort

00:33:42.058 --> 00:33:43.547
of thing,
but also he says,

00:33:43.547 --> 00:33:47.521
you're going to have to suffer;
they're going to hand you over

00:33:47.521 --> 00:33:48.848
for persecution.
 

00:33:48.848 --> 00:33:52.656
In 13:10, "And the good
news must first be proclaimed to

00:33:52.656 --> 00:33:55.828
all nations,"
so Jesus is predicting that,

00:33:55.828 --> 00:33:57.808
before the end comes,
his message,

00:33:57.808 --> 00:34:01.670
the Gospel message,
will be proclaimed all around.

00:34:01.670 --> 00:34:04.200
Even though you have worse
things happening,

00:34:04.200 --> 00:34:06.113
13:12:
Brother will betray brother to

00:34:06.113 --> 00:34:08.697
death, a father his child,
and children will rise against

00:34:08.697 --> 00:34:10.449
parents and have them put to
death;

00:34:10.449 --> 00:34:12.856
and you will be hated by all
because of my name,

00:34:12.856 --> 00:34:15.469
but the one who endures to the
end will be saved.

00:34:15.469 --> 00:34:18.152
In other words,
familial divisions even,

00:34:18.152 --> 00:34:21.663
that households will be torn
apart by the suffering,

00:34:21.663 --> 00:34:23.039
by the conflict.
 

00:34:23.039 --> 00:34:27.143
Then 13:14, "But when you
see the desolating sacrilege set

00:34:27.143 --> 00:34:30.518
up where it ought not to
be," now here's one of

00:34:30.518 --> 00:34:33.829
those little phrases,
"Let the reader

00:34:33.829 --> 00:34:35.260
understand."
 

00:34:35.260 --> 00:34:38.103
The author is giving you a
very, very clear clue that this

00:34:38.103 --> 00:34:40.550
is when you really better be
paying attention,

00:34:40.550 --> 00:34:42.889
"let the reader
understand."

00:34:42.889 --> 00:34:45.070
"When you see the
desolating sacrilege set up

00:34:45.070 --> 00:34:46.539
where it ought not to be."
 

00:34:46.539 --> 00:34:47.800
Have we heard that before?
 

00:34:47.800 --> 00:34:51.193
The abomination of desolation
is the King James English

00:34:51.193 --> 00:34:52.449
translation of it.
 

00:34:52.449 --> 00:34:55.195
The desolating sacrilege is
often what is translated in more

00:34:55.195 --> 00:34:57.396
modern Bibles;
it all refers to the same

00:34:57.396 --> 00:34:57.980
language.
 

00:34:57.980 --> 00:35:00.663
Where have we heard about the
abomination of desolation being

00:35:00.663 --> 00:35:02.809
set up where it ought not to be
set up before?

00:35:02.809 --> 00:35:06.750
Daniel;
the words come right out of

00:35:06.750 --> 00:35:07.420
Daniel.
 

00:35:07.420 --> 00:35:10.398
They occur three--Daniel was
written in a combination of

00:35:10.398 --> 00:35:13.702
Hebrew and Aramaic and this is
in Greek, but this is the Greek

00:35:13.702 --> 00:35:14.570
translation.
 

00:35:14.570 --> 00:35:17.710
You have it in Daniel 9:27,
Daniel 11:31,

00:35:17.710 --> 00:35:21.085
and Daniel 12:11,
so this Jesus has read his

00:35:21.085 --> 00:35:21.949
Daniel.
 

00:35:21.949 --> 00:35:27.579
Then you have warnings and
woes, verses 15 through 13,

00:35:27.579 --> 00:35:30.659
so you have all this stuff.
 

00:35:30.659 --> 00:35:32.650
What happens after that?
 

00:35:32.650 --> 00:35:35.820
The one on the housetop must
not go down into house and take

00:35:35.820 --> 00:35:37.797
anything away;
the one in the field must not

00:35:37.797 --> 00:35:38.840
turn back to get the coat.
 

00:35:38.840 --> 00:35:40.806
Woe to those who are pregnant,
to those who are nursing

00:35:40.806 --> 00:35:41.679
infants in those days!
 

00:35:41.679 --> 00:35:43.039
Pray that it may not be in
winter.

00:35:43.039 --> 00:35:45.291
For in those days there will be
suffering such as not had been

00:35:45.291 --> 00:35:46.880
from the beginning of creation
that God .

00:35:46.880 --> 00:35:47.610
and never will be.
 

00:35:47.610 --> 00:35:49.344
And if the Lord had not cut
short those days,

00:35:49.344 --> 00:35:50.289
no one would be saved.
 

00:35:50.289 --> 00:35:53.989
Now notice, we're not getting
any more historical events here,

00:35:53.989 --> 00:35:56.427
we're not getting any more
stuff happening except right

00:35:56.427 --> 00:35:57.974
then he says,
"If anyone says to you,

00:35:57.974 --> 00:35:58.179
'Look!
 

00:35:58.179 --> 00:35:58.809
Here is the Messiah!'
 

00:35:58.809 --> 00:35:59.380
or 'Look!
 

00:35:59.380 --> 00:36:00.300
There he is!'--do not believe
it."

00:36:00.300 --> 00:36:01.597
False Messiahs,
false prophets,

00:36:01.597 --> 00:36:03.630
so there's more false besides
false prophets.

00:36:03.630 --> 00:36:05.702
"In those days after that
suffering,"

00:36:05.702 --> 00:36:08.001
now here's where you really get
the cataclysmic end,

00:36:08.001 --> 00:36:10.420
the world crashing down:
The sun will be darkened,

00:36:10.420 --> 00:36:12.956
the moon will not give its
light, and stars will fall from

00:36:12.956 --> 00:36:15.579
the skies, and the powers in the
heavens will be shaken.

00:36:15.579 --> 00:36:20.199
Then you will see the Son of
Man coming in clouds with great

00:36:20.199 --> 00:36:21.610
glory and power.
 

00:36:21.610 --> 00:36:24.052
Then he will send out the
angels, and gather his elect

00:36:24.052 --> 00:36:26.309
from the four winds,
from the ends of the earth to

00:36:26.309 --> 00:36:27.369
the ends of heaven.
 

00:36:27.369 --> 00:36:29.480
When does it happen?
 

00:36:29.480 --> 00:36:33.708
Right after the abomination of
desolation is set up where it

00:36:33.708 --> 00:36:35.000
ought not to be.
 

00:36:35.000 --> 00:36:36.659
What is the abomination of
desolation?

00:36:36.659 --> 00:36:38.039
Well, we don't know.
 

00:36:38.039 --> 00:36:41.452
Obviously if Jesus is reading
Daniel, and this is where he's

00:36:41.452 --> 00:36:43.418
getting this,
he also believes that

00:36:43.418 --> 00:36:46.079
something's going to happen in
the temple.

00:36:46.079 --> 00:36:49.307
That author Daniel believed it
was something that Antiochus IV

00:36:49.307 --> 00:36:52.007
Epiphanes may be sacrificed a
pig on the altar or he

00:36:52.007 --> 00:36:54.971
desecrated somehow the altar in
the Holy of Holies in the

00:36:54.971 --> 00:36:55.659
temple.
 

00:36:55.659 --> 00:36:58.826
Jesus doesn't believe that that
event was the end event as

00:36:58.826 --> 00:37:00.159
Daniel thought it was.
 

00:37:00.159 --> 00:37:02.630
Jesus is predicting that this
is going to happen,

00:37:02.630 --> 00:37:04.588
something's going to happen in
the temple that is going to be

00:37:04.588 --> 00:37:06.626
so awful,
and it's going to be an

00:37:06.626 --> 00:37:09.500
abomination,
and once that happens then all

00:37:09.500 --> 00:37:13.489
hell breaks loose and when all
hell is broken loose the worst,

00:37:13.489 --> 00:37:17.179
then the Son of Man will swoop
down in the clouds with angels

00:37:17.179 --> 00:37:18.840
and put a stop to it all.
 

00:37:18.840 --> 00:37:22.480
That'll be the glorification.
 

00:37:22.480 --> 00:37:24.530
When does this happen?
 

00:37:24.530 --> 00:37:26.827
Well Mark has told us one
thing: it's going to happen

00:37:26.827 --> 00:37:28.110
during your own generation.
 

00:37:28.110 --> 00:37:30.070
Jesus has said,
"This generation will not

00:37:30.070 --> 00:37:31.989
pass away before this stuff
happens."

00:37:31.989 --> 00:37:34.693
The apostles asked him,
so he said, "Well it will

00:37:34.693 --> 00:37:35.969
be within a generation.
 

00:37:35.969 --> 00:37:37.581
Then he says,
nobody's going to know the

00:37:37.581 --> 00:37:38.920
exact time,
but once you see the

00:37:38.920 --> 00:37:41.358
abomination of desolation set up
in the temple where it ought not

00:37:41.358 --> 00:37:42.617
to be,
that's when it's going to

00:37:42.617 --> 00:37:42.900
happen.
 

00:37:42.900 --> 00:37:45.949
Now did this happen?
 

00:37:45.949 --> 00:37:51.090
Well, we're not narrated
anything about it.

00:37:51.090 --> 00:37:55.775
What does Mark not narrate in
this section that we as

00:37:55.775 --> 00:37:59.650
historians know happened with
the temple?

00:37:59.650 --> 00:38:02.460
What?
 

00:38:02.460 --> 00:38:05.989
What does he not narrate
happening?

00:38:05.989 --> 00:38:07.940
Its destruction.
 

00:38:07.940 --> 00:38:11.465
Jesus predicts the destruction,
Jesus prophesied about

00:38:11.465 --> 00:38:15.126
destruction, but Mark doesn't
tell us that the temple in

00:38:15.126 --> 00:38:16.989
Jerusalem are destroyed.
 

00:38:16.989 --> 00:38:21.032
He doesn't tell us explicitly
about the Roman armies led by

00:38:21.032 --> 00:38:25.284
Vespasian and Titus surrounding
Jerusalem and besieging it for

00:38:25.284 --> 00:38:26.260
two years.
 

00:38:26.260 --> 00:38:30.867
He doesn't tell us that in the
year 70, the Romans actually did

00:38:30.867 --> 00:38:35.030
take Jerusalem and burn the
temple destroy the temple.

00:38:35.030 --> 00:38:38.070
If Mark knew about that why
didn't he tell us about it?

00:38:38.070 --> 00:38:41.186
This is why scholars--a lot of
scholars believe this is exactly

00:38:41.186 --> 00:38:41.889
like Daniel.
 

00:38:41.889 --> 00:38:44.070
Remember how we said,
how do you date Daniel?

00:38:44.070 --> 00:38:48.409
You figure out when does has
his history gone right?

00:38:48.409 --> 00:38:51.139
When does his history not go
right anymore?

00:38:51.139 --> 00:38:55.239
If you applied that same
standard of text to this text,

00:38:55.239 --> 00:38:58.210
what you've got is a prediction
of the temple destruction,

00:38:58.210 --> 00:39:01.530
so at least the writer knows
that it is likely to happen.

00:39:01.530 --> 00:39:04.454
He can see it happening in the
future but he doesn't narrate it

00:39:04.454 --> 00:39:05.019
happening.
 

00:39:05.019 --> 00:39:06.050
Yes sir?
 

00:39:06.050 --> 00:39:09.518
Student:  I was just
wondering about a timeline;

00:39:09.518 --> 00:39:11.632
the version I have has "a
generation"

00:39:11.632 --> 00:39:13.380
translated also as
"race."

00:39:13.380 --> 00:39:14.400
Prof: Yes.
 

00:39:14.400 --> 00:39:20.521
Conservative Christians know
that more than one generation

00:39:20.521 --> 00:39:25.130
has happened since that time;
many, many, many generations.

00:39:25.130 --> 00:39:27.454
They've taken the Greek word
translated here as

00:39:27.454 --> 00:39:29.929
"generation,"
which I think is the right

00:39:29.929 --> 00:39:31.666
translation,
and they say well,

00:39:31.666 --> 00:39:34.639
you can take that to
mean "race of people."

00:39:34.639 --> 00:39:37.420
Of course what race would they
then be referring too?

00:39:37.420 --> 00:39:41.300
The Jews, and so conservative
Christians who don't believe--

00:39:41.300 --> 00:39:43.532
who believe this has to be an
accurate prediction of something

00:39:43.532 --> 00:39:45.179
that's going to happen in our
future also,

00:39:45.179 --> 00:39:48.333
translate that as race or say,
the generation doesn't refer to

00:39:48.333 --> 00:39:50.659
a generation of time of forty
years or so,

00:39:50.659 --> 00:39:52.530
it means they're a race of the
Jews.

00:39:52.530 --> 00:39:55.599
As long as there are Jews in
existence then this thing can

00:39:55.599 --> 00:39:57.646
still go on and it hasn't
happened yet,

00:39:57.646 --> 00:39:59.639
so that explains the
translation.

00:39:59.639 --> 00:40:03.175
Quite frankly,
I think the translation's just

00:40:03.175 --> 00:40:03.820
wrong.
 

00:40:03.820 --> 00:40:07.570
It seems to me that what Mark's
intention is to put some kind of

00:40:07.570 --> 00:40:08.820
time limit on this.
 

00:40:08.820 --> 00:40:10.659
He's trying to get his readers
to see a time.

00:40:10.659 --> 00:40:13.911
Well if you just say the race
of the Jews, then that doesn't

00:40:13.911 --> 00:40:15.510
give you any sense of time.
 

00:40:15.510 --> 00:40:17.880
Did you have a question?
 

00:40:17.880 --> 00:40:22.570
Okay, so where are we now?
 

00:40:22.570 --> 00:40:24.657
I think what's going on is
this, let's just think

00:40:24.657 --> 00:40:25.920
of--imagine this happening.
 

00:40:25.920 --> 00:40:29.090
16:1-8 I've already read.
 

00:40:29.090 --> 00:40:31.550
What happens in 16:1-8?
 

00:40:31.550 --> 00:40:34.309
The women are told that Jesus
has been raised from the dead,

00:40:34.309 --> 00:40:38.681
as Jesus predicted he would be,
and the young man tells the

00:40:38.681 --> 00:40:41.052
women,
go tell his disciples that he

00:40:41.052 --> 00:40:44.170
will go before them to Galilee,
go meet him in Galilee.

00:40:44.170 --> 00:40:46.989
In fact earlier,
in Mark, in one of these sorts

00:40:46.989 --> 00:40:50.175
of passion predictions,
Jesus had told the disciples,

00:40:50.175 --> 00:40:53.239
once I'm dead I will go before
you to Galilee.

00:40:53.239 --> 00:40:56.706
Implying that they're supposed
to follow him to Galilee,

00:40:56.706 --> 00:40:58.030
but then 16:8 ends.
 

00:40:58.030 --> 00:41:00.429
One possible reconstruction for
all of this,

00:41:00.429 --> 00:41:02.557
and this is just an
interpretation put out by some

00:41:02.557 --> 00:41:03.900
scholars,
accepted by some,

00:41:03.900 --> 00:41:05.590
rejected by a whole lot of
others.

00:41:05.590 --> 00:41:10.230
What if Mark himself is writing
right before the year 70?

00:41:10.230 --> 00:41:13.617
He knows--maybe he's even
writing in Galilee himself,

00:41:13.617 --> 00:41:15.900
or in someplace close to
Galilee.

00:41:15.900 --> 00:41:19.556
He knows--the Roman army went
through Galilee first in the

00:41:19.556 --> 00:41:22.510
year 66 and 68 and destroyed
lots of stuff,

00:41:22.510 --> 00:41:26.331
and they won their battles
against the Jews in Galilee

00:41:26.331 --> 00:41:26.909
first.
 

00:41:26.909 --> 00:41:29.476
They won through Galilee on
their way to Jerusalem,

00:41:29.476 --> 00:41:32.402
they get to Jerusalem around
68, and for two years they're

00:41:32.402 --> 00:41:34.250
besieging the city of Jerusalem.
 

00:41:34.250 --> 00:41:36.309
What if Mark has written right
at that time,

00:41:36.309 --> 00:41:38.460
before Jerusalem had actually
been taken,

00:41:38.460 --> 00:41:40.530
before the temple had actually
been destroyed,

00:41:40.530 --> 00:41:43.420
because he has Jesus predict,
like Daniel predicted,

00:41:43.420 --> 00:41:45.670
some abomination of desolation
happening in the temple,

00:41:45.670 --> 00:41:47.715
but we don't know of anything
like that really that happened

00:41:47.715 --> 00:41:48.929
as a historical event right
then.

00:41:48.929 --> 00:41:52.059
The temple was simply destroyed
by the Romans.

00:41:52.059 --> 00:41:54.123
We might think,
well maybe he thinks that

00:41:54.123 --> 00:41:57.530
they're going to set up a Roman
standard there or do something,

00:41:57.530 --> 00:41:59.559
but we're not narrated what
actually happened.

00:41:59.559 --> 00:42:04.440
In this scenario Mark writes
his Gospel with this message,

00:42:04.440 --> 00:42:08.333
"Things are going to get a
lot worse before they get

00:42:08.333 --> 00:42:10.742
better,
and just like they got a lot

00:42:10.742 --> 00:42:13.250
worse for Jesus before they got
better,

00:42:13.250 --> 00:42:16.559
they're going to get a lot
worse for us before they get

00:42:16.559 --> 00:42:17.480
better."
 

00:42:17.480 --> 00:42:20.396
You need to be prepared,
because if you think that the

00:42:20.396 --> 00:42:23.478
Romans are going to win and
we're all going to be carried

00:42:23.478 --> 00:42:26.460
off into slavery,
you don't have the right faith.

00:42:26.460 --> 00:42:28.449
Jesus told us this.
 

00:42:28.449 --> 00:42:30.905
Jesus told us it wouldn't be
all pie in the sky by and by,

00:42:30.905 --> 00:42:33.449
it wouldn't be all good stuff,
we're going to have to suffer

00:42:33.449 --> 00:42:34.570
just like He suffered.
 

00:42:34.570 --> 00:42:39.233
He writes this Gospel message
that over and over again has

00:42:39.233 --> 00:42:42.670
Jesus saying,
suffering must precede glory,

00:42:42.670 --> 00:42:45.369
suffering must precede glory.
 

00:42:45.369 --> 00:42:48.554
He even has Jesus predict
around the time when all this

00:42:48.554 --> 00:42:51.009
will happen,
when you see Jerusalem--if

00:42:51.009 --> 00:42:54.449
Jerusalem is surrounded by Roman
armies who are pagans,

00:42:54.449 --> 00:42:58.639
you can pretty well guess that
something's going to happen.

00:42:58.639 --> 00:43:01.873
I believe that the Gospel of
Mark may have been written right

00:43:01.873 --> 00:43:05.045
before 70 or right around 70,
but the destruction of the

00:43:05.045 --> 00:43:07.882
temple has not sunk into
consciousness yet or is not

00:43:07.882 --> 00:43:08.940
known to happen.
 

00:43:08.940 --> 00:43:12.744
Maybe even Mark himself and his
disciples are themselves in

00:43:12.744 --> 00:43:13.400
Galilee.
 

00:43:13.400 --> 00:43:16.489
Maybe this is why he says,
we're supposed to be Galilee

00:43:16.489 --> 00:43:19.409
waiting for Jesus,
and then He will appear to us.

00:43:19.409 --> 00:43:21.447
When all is worse,
when it just seems like

00:43:21.447 --> 00:43:25.137
everything couldn't get worse,
I tell you he's going to come

00:43:25.137 --> 00:43:28.530
in on the clouds and he'll
destroy the Romans,

00:43:28.530 --> 00:43:30.550
and he'll set up the Kingdom of
God.

00:43:30.550 --> 00:43:33.739
If he's doing this it makes a
lot of sense for the document

00:43:33.739 --> 00:43:35.280
also ending where it ends.
 

00:43:35.280 --> 00:43:39.650
It says, "Tell them to go
to Galilee and wait,"

00:43:39.650 --> 00:43:42.849
and Jesus goes to Galilee to
meet them.

00:43:42.849 --> 00:43:47.632
In a sense, Mark's telling his
readers, all we have to do is

00:43:47.632 --> 00:43:50.389
stay here and he'll come for us.
 

00:43:50.389 --> 00:43:54.990
That's one historical reading
of the Gospel of Mark that

00:43:54.990 --> 00:43:58.170
places it in one,
not provable time;

00:43:58.170 --> 00:43:59.960
some scholars believe Mark was
written in Rome.

00:43:59.960 --> 00:44:02.949
Some people believe it was
written after 70.

00:44:02.949 --> 00:44:05.670
I would say if Mark was written
70,

00:44:05.670 --> 00:44:08.088
very long after 70,
I would clearly expect him to

00:44:08.088 --> 00:44:11.012
narrate the destruction of
Jerusalem and the destruction of

00:44:11.012 --> 00:44:13.230
the temple,
as Luke does.

00:44:13.230 --> 00:44:15.876
When you read Luke,
who used Mark as one of his

00:44:15.876 --> 00:44:18.250
sources,
you'll notice that the writer

00:44:18.250 --> 00:44:22.030
of the Gospel of Luke uses this
passage out of Mark and he edits

00:44:22.030 --> 00:44:25.219
it,
to add in the destruction of

00:44:25.219 --> 00:44:28.780
the temple before Jesus comes
back.

00:44:28.780 --> 00:44:29.920
The reason?
 

00:44:29.920 --> 00:44:32.143
Because the writer of Luke knew
that the temple had been

00:44:32.143 --> 00:44:32.630
destroyed.
 

00:44:32.630 --> 00:44:34.260
Why doesn't Mark tell about it?
 

00:44:34.260 --> 00:44:36.019
Because he doesn't know yet
that it's been destroyed.

